Facinet Keita was representing Guinea in the 2012 Olympics when he was knocked out in the qualifying stages . 
  He fled the Olympic village in London claiming he 'would be murdered' if he returned to Guinea . 
  He claims his coaches told him he lost the fight 'like a baby' He was jailed for three months but is refusing to leave the UK after two asylum bids were rejected . 
  He is now applying for his third asylum application in the UK . 
 